          "date": "2013-06-14 09:00:06.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-3335 scrub: rebuild LAST_ID",
        "message": "LU-3335 scrub: rebuild LAST_ID\n\nThe /O/<seq>/LAST_ID records the last oid of the object allocated\nwithin the sequence. The LAST_ID file can be crashed or missed as\nthe system running. The OI scrub can detect the LAST_ID lost case\nwhen initial OI scrub (at mount), and can rebuild the LAST_ID via\nscanning the whole device.\n\nThis functionality is also part of LU-14 live replacement of OST.\n\nTest-Parameters: testlist=sanity-scrub\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I0b1062418b000e569a29805c155055866557126e\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
